# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# What this .gitignore protects:
#
# ✅ COMMITTED (so anyone cloning gets a working starting state):
#    - All source files, config, scripts, docs
#    - Empty template versions of applications-log.csv, seen-jobs.csv,
#      session-state.json (just headers / empty JSON — no personal data)
#    - Placeholder folders (Resume/, cover-letters/, browser-profile/)
#      via .gitkeep so the directory structure exists on clone
#
# ❌ NOT COMMITTED (would either bloat the repo or leak personal data):
#    - node_modules/  → huge, auto-generated by `npm install`
#    - Your resume    → personal
#    - browser-profile/ contents → contains your LinkedIn cookies + Google
#      session. Committing these would let anyone log in as you. NEVER push.
#    - Generated cover letters → per-job, per-user output
#    - ats-accounts.txt → may contain account/email info
#    - Screenshots and debug artifacts
#
# Note: once you start running the agent, applications-log.csv / seen-jobs.csv
# / session-state.json will get personal data appended. Those committed files
# are *template starting states* — don't push your modified versions unless you
# explicitly want your job-application history in a public repo.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Dependencies — regenerated by `npm install`
node_modules/

# Personal resume — recipients drop their own into Resume/
Resume/*.pdf
Resume/*.docx
*Resume*.pdf
*Resume*.docx
*resume*.pdf
*resume*.docx

# Per-user runtime state that may contain sensitive info
ats-accounts.txt
scheduled-runs.log

# Generated cover letters (per-job, per-user)
cover-letters/*.txt
cover-letters/*.md
!cover-letters/.gitkeep

# Persistent browser profiles — contain LinkedIn cookies, Google session,
# ATS logins. NEVER commit (anyone could log in as you). Covers every per-persona
# profile folder (browser-profile-<persona>) + any snapshots/backups.
browser-profile/*
!browser-profile/.gitkeep
browser-profile-*/

# Playwright MCP scratch
.playwright-mcp/

# Local Claude Code settings (per-user)
.claude/settings.local.json

# Screenshots / debug artifacts
*.png
*.jpeg
*.jpg

# Local recovery backups created during runs (not the source of truth — the live
# seen-jobs.csv / applications-log.csv are). Keep the repo clean of these.
*.bak.csv
*.backup.csv
*.backup2.csv
*.backup.json
*.bak.json
dryrun-*.txt
